The new Emir of Kano, Aminu Ado Bayero, was born in 1961. He attended Kofar Kudu Primary School in Kano Municipal and thereafter Birnin Kudu Secondary School in the present Jigawa State before he proceeded to Bayero University Kano where he obtained a degree in mass communication. Bayero also studied at Aviation School Oakland in California, USA and did his National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) at Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) Makurdi, Benue State. After his national service, Bayero was employed by Kabo Air Limited. The emir was turbaned as Dan Majen Kano and District Head of Dala Local Government in 1990 when his late father, Ado Bayero celebrated his 60 years anniversary. In the same year, his late father married for him two wives at the same time. The new emir held several traditional titles before he was appointed the first Emir of Bichi emirate. He started as Dan Majen Kano, then Danburan Kano, Turakin Kano, Sarkin Dawaki Tsakar Gida and then Wamban Kano. The last hours of Emir of Kano Ado Bayero Sanusi takes throne as Emir of Kano Ciroman Kano: The Road Not Taken by Sanusi Bayero